CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 22, 1958, pg. 23, reads: Growling Bulldogs - The Bulldogs of Westinghouse High School, above, are favored to retain the city football championship Friday night at South High School Stadium against Allegheny High. Members of the team are, left to right, front row: Anthony Liscio, end; Howard Hosbey, tackle; Raymond Miller, tackle; Robert Marshall, tackle; Lyde Evans, guard; Kenny DeHonney, center, and Ralph Young, guard.   Back row: Pete Dimperio, head coach; Eugene McClellan, right half; Ronald Henderson, quarterback; Frank Battista, end; Mike Bisceglia, fullback; Albert Calloway, left half, and Bruce Weston, assistant coach. - Harris Photo.
TitMainTitle: Westinghouse High School football team, front row from left: Anthony "Tony" Liscio, Howard "Howdy" Hosbey, Raymond Miller, Robert "Bob" Marshall, Lyde Evans, Kenny DeHonney, Ralph Young; second row: coach Pete Dimperio, Eugene McClellan, Ronald "Ronnie" Henderson, Frank Battista, Mike Bisceglia, Albert "Skippy" Calloway, and assistant coach Bruce Weston
